fields.descriptive_line: Sketchbook containing designs for textiles, wall-papers and various decorative motifs, a design for a London house and two floral designs by Beatrice Godwin.  Pencil, pen and ink, water-colour and gouache drawings by Edward William Godwin, 1876-1878.  172 pages of squared paper and three inserted leaves of metallic surfaced paper, full-bound in leather, edged with brass, with a pencil holder.
fields.physical_description: Sketchbook containing designs for textiles, wallpapers and various decorative motifs, and a design for a London house with ship and office accommodation. 172 pages of squared paper and three inserted leaves of metallic surfaced paper, also two inserted leaves with floral designs. Full-bound in leather, edged with brass, with a pencil holder.

fields.bibliography: Victoria and Albert Museum Department of Prints and Drawings and Department of Paintings, Accessions 1963 . London: HMSO, 1964. The full text of the entry is as follows: "GODWIN, Edward William, F.S.A. (1833-1886) Sketch-book containing designs for textiles, wall-papers and various decorative motifs, and a design for a London house with shop and office accommodation. Also two floral designs by Beatrice Godwin. 172 pages of squared paper and three inserted leaves of metallic surfaced paper, full-bound in leather, edged with brass, with a pencil holder. 1876-78. Signed and dated on the fly-leaf E W Godwin. Aug 18 1876. Inscribed throughout with notes, including a list of the artist's designs taken to Sweden by Mr. Constable, details of plates for W. Watt's 'Art Furniture from Designs by E. W. Godwin…', references, sale details etc. Dated 18 August to 31 July 1878. Signed on p.152 with monogram BG. Pencil, pen and ink, water- and body-colour. Size of volume 10.8 x 15.9 cm. E.241-1963 Given by Mr. Edward Godwin, son of the artist" Katagami Style Exhibition catalogue, 2012
fields.credit: Given by Mr Edward Godwin, son of the artist
